---
description: Modular backend and package architecture rules
globs:
  - "packages/**"
  - "app/main/**"
  - "engine/**"
  - "native/**"
alwaysApply: false
---

- Keep module ownership and dependency direction explicit: contract → application service → port → adapter.
- Renderer/UI code never imports infrastructure adapters; infrastructure never imports renderer code.
- Keep the composition root in Electron main and reject circular dependencies.
- Do not create global utility dumping grounds or a package for one small private helper.
- A new package needs a purpose, public API, errors, lifecycle, dependency policy, and focused tests.
- Review every new dependency for license, install behavior, size, and removal path.
- Separate move-only refactors from behavior changes when practical.
